Gujarat Mineral Development Corporation Limited (GMDC) is a major minerals and lignite mining company of India. It is a state owned company. GMDC was founded in 1963. Its corporate headquarters is at Ahmedabad.
Its product range includes essential energy minerals like lignite, base metals and industrial minerals like bauxite and flourspar. Gujarat government as given its green signal to GMDC to form a joint venture with NALCO for a 1 mtpa refinery.
GMDC also owns and runs Akrimota Thermal Power Station a 250 MW (2x125 MW) lignite-based thermal power plant located in village Nanichher in Lakhpat Taluka, Kutch District.
